Next.js routing is file-based where () groups are only for organization and don’t affect URLs, while [] defines dynamic segments that match any path and pass values to your page, with static routes always taking priority over dynamic ones; since Next doesn’t natively route by subdomain, your multi-tenant setup requires middleware to extract the tenant from the subdomain (e.g., acme), attach it (like via x-tenant), and rewrite requests internally (e.g., /about → /_tenant/about) so tenant pages are separated from main site pages without changing the browser URL; then Next simply resolves the correct page file, and that page calls your Nest API (e.g., /page?tenant=acme&page=about) to fetch JSON that your visualizer renders, while returning notFound() if the page doesn’t exist.

you need now an extractor to extract the page the user wants to route it to its respective page